The paper deals with the study of networks and centrality measures, which are commonly used in the fields of social informatics (cs.SI), data mining (cs.DM), social network analysis (cs.SD), network infrastructure (cs.NI), and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper's focus on the ability of different centrality measures to distinguish vertices in a network suggests that it may be relevant to these sub-categories.
